{\pard\plain \li0\sl259\slmult1 \ri240\nooverflow\ql\fi480 {\f1\fs20 In 1987, an exciting breakthrough in the field of methamphetamine manufacture occurred. This new development was so important because it promised to completely turn the tables on the DEA-led chemical blockaders and controllers. The new discovery was a patent issued in that year covering a simple and quick method for converting allylbenzene into phenylacetone. This method is exquisitely suited for clandestine operations, and is easily scaled up to industrial proportions.}\par}
