{\pard\sl-89\slmult0\par

{\pard\plain \li0\sl263\slmult1 \ri0\nooverflow\ql\fi480 {\f1\fs20 To use the bomb, the reactants are added to the bomb with a funnel through the faucet. If any sodium acetate is left clinging to the valve, it will prevent a good seal. The Raney nickel is added with a pipette. When the reaction is over, the products are siphoned out with a bent section of glass tubing. Vacuum from an aspirator speeds up this process considerably, as does using large-diameter tubing.}\par}
}
